[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sussex v Leicestershire: Stiaan van Zyl's unbeaten 166 sets Foxes 425 to win

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sussex's Stiaan van Zyl scored an unbeaten 166 as Leicestershire ended day three 36-0 chasing 425 to win.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The South African struck 24 boundaries, sharing century partnerships with Luke Wright (60) and Ben Brown (67), as Sussex moved their score on from 74-1.
Jofra Archer then smashed four sixes and three fours to score 42 off 14 balls as Sussex declared on 443-6.
Leicestershire openers Paul Horton and Arun Harinath reached stumps unbeaten, leaving 389 runs to score on day four.
